Introduction
Cognism Limited has prepared this Privacy Policy to describe: (i) what personal information or personal data (“personal data”) we collect, (ii) how we use and share personal data and (iii) your choices in relation to our privacy and personal data practices.
If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Telephone: +44 20 3858 0822
Email:
privacy@cognism.com
Registered address:
Cognism Limited,
C/O Worldwide Corporate Advisors, 150 Minories, London, England, EC3N 1LS
PLEASE NOTE
: IF YOU ARE A RESIDENT OF US STATES WITH PRIVACY LAWS CLICK
HERE
FOR OUR US STATE-SPECIFIC PRIVACY POLICY TO FIND OUT MORE ABOUT YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS UNDER THE APPLICABLE STATE LAW(S).
Applicability
We provide a suite of products and services pursuant to the respective order document to our customers
(“Customers”
) on a software-as-a-service basis, such as our sales intelligence platform (the “
Cognism
Platform
”) or our applications (e.g. browser extensions) (collectively referred to as the “
Services
”). This Privacy Policy applies to personal data that we collect, use, disclose and otherwise process in connection with the Services, our website(s) (including https://www.cognism.com/)
(“
Website
”),
and any other products and/or services that specifically link to this Privacy Policy, from you, public sources or third-party vendors.
If you are a Customer of Cognism, this Privacy Policy does not apply to personal data that we process on your behalf (if any) as your service provider. Such personal data shall instead be governed by the terms and conditions of the separate customer agreement or terms of service that you have agreed to with Cognism.
Our Services are designed for businesses and are not intended for personal, family, or household use. Accordingly, we treat all personal data covered by this Privacy Policy as pertaining to individuals acting as business representatives, rather than in their personal capacity.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully as it will help you make informed decisions about sharing your personal information with us and exercising your rights under the applicable laws.
You can exercise your right to opt-out at any time from the Cognism Platform in the Cognism
Privacy Centre
. For more information, please refer to Section 9.
1. WHO IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE PROCESSING OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
Cognism, as data controller
Cognism acts as a data controller, as described in this Privacy Policy, when we collect and use information about data subjects who are visitors to our Website and Services, as well as when we collect and use information about data subjects for purposes of creating, providing and maintaining our Services.
our Customers, as data controller
When our Customers use our Services, they are acting as the data controller and are responsible for ensuring that personal information collected about data subjects is being processed lawfully, and specifically, for:
ensuring that personal information collected about data subjects is being processed lawfully;
determining whether and how they wish to use our Services, and for ensuring that all third-party individuals that are a visitor to or user of a website, application, or service on which a Customer uses our Services have been provided with adequate notice regarding the processing of their personal information, have given informed consent where such consent is necessary or advised, and that all legal requirements applicable to the collection, use, or other processing of personal information through our services have been met by such Customers;
handling data subject rights requests under applicable law, by their users and other individuals whose data they process through the services.
In the context of and depending on the Services provided to our Customers, Cognism may either be controller or processor.
