Data regarding our Website visitors and Customers
Purposes
Examples of use of your personal data
Legal bases
Online requests, communications and advertising
Managing your enquiries
to process your enquiries (demo or contact requests, etc.)
to reply and provide support, including providing you and/or your organisation with information about the Services.
Our legitimate interest
to manage our users, prospective clients and Customers enquiries
Direct marketing communications and advertising
to send postal, phone, electronic or email communications to our Customers and prospective Customers, including via our mailing list with information on news, offers, and updates about Cognism (see Section 9 of this Privacy Policy) for how to unsubscribe);
to conduct remarketing for Cognism, which allows us to show Cognism ads to people who’ve previously visited our website;
to conduct advertising on social networks for Cognism, which means that if you link to one of our social media platforms you may be subject to targeted marketing displaying Cognism ads via that site.
Our legitimate interest
to develop our business activities with professionals.
If required by applicable law, we will request
your consent
for electronic marketing communications.
