5. WHO DO WE SHARE YOUR DATA WITH?
We will share your information, on a limited and need-to-know basis, with the following recipients:
Recipients
Purposes
Cognism and its duly authorized employees
For the administrative, operational and commercial management of the Website and Services as indicated in Section 4 of this Privacy Policy.
Other Cognism affiliates
For the global management of the Website and Services operated by Cognism, where the Cognism affiliates (
Cognism Inc (US), Cognism Software BC Ltd (Canada), Cognism d.o.o (Croatia), Cognism DOOEL Skopje (Macedonia), NESTAG GmbH (Germany), Cognism GmbH (Germany), Mailtastic Limited (UK), KASPR SAS (France)) can act as processors or subprocessors, respectively.
As applicable, for transmitting the employment application to the Cognism entity concerned by the employment offer, so the Cognism entity can examine your employment application and contact you.
Cognism Customers
Business contacts data is provided to the Customers (or their customers), as part of the offering of our Services, through limited access to the Cognism Platform, and/or disclosure to a Customer’s software or solutions as requested or directed by our Customers.
The Customers process this data as data controllers for the purposes summarized in Section 4 of this Privacy Policy, as further described in their privacy policies. By remaining in the Cognism Platform, you may be contacted by our Customers, as data controllers, when they are conducting their business-to-business sales, marketing, and recruiting activities.
Suppliers, subcontractors, service providers
For operational and technical purposes related to operating the Website and its Services, insofar as is necessary for suppliers, subcontractors and service providers to assist us in carrying out business activities.
This category includes external third-party service providers, such as outside professional advisors, IT systems, support and hosting service providers, technical engineers, data storage and cloud providers and similar third-party vendors and outsourced service providers.
Professional advisers and all interested parties
Exclusively in the case of the management of possible disputes and other legal matters where appropriate.
Administrative or judiciary authorities
Exclusively in case of an express and justified request from them or in case of an alleged violation of legal or regulatory provisions, and to establish, exercise or defend our legal rights (including providing information to others for the purposes of fraud prevention).
Other third parties such as potential acquirers or investors
If we are involved in a restructuring operation, merger, acquisition, sale of all or a portion of our assets or a similar transaction, as well as in case of insolvency, bankruptcy or receivership, where personal data are transferred to one or more third parties as assets of Cognism.
6. WILL YOUR PERSONAL DATA BE TRANSFERRED OUTSIDE OF THE EUROPEAN UNION/EUROPEAN ECONOMIC AREA?
As far as possible, your personal data will be stored and kept inside the UK, Switzerland and the European Economic Area (together, the “
EEA
”). However, due to the nature of our global business and the technologies required, your personal data may be transferred to third party service providers, Customers or affiliates outside the EEA, in third countries.
In the event that the third country does not ensure a adequate level of protection of personal data, Cognism ensures that the appropriate safeguards to protect your personal data (in particular standard contractual clauses) in the absence of a decision of adequacy and after having carried out an assessment of the level of protection of your rights in the third country.
A copy of such safeguards can be obtained by sending an email directly to Cognism (see contact details in the introduction of this Privacy Policy).
